INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','zagalejo','Over the skirt is worn: on the front, the mandila, made of black cloth that practically covers the velvet farraco, and, on the back, the so-called large embroidered black velvet back ribbon. Unlike the manteo, the zagalejo does not wear a mantilla, but instead wears a bun ribbon that is placed over the bun, a characteristic hairstyle of this suit.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','sayas','It is said that the serrano suits are a lesser evolution of the "traje de manteo". The "sayas" costume is possibly the simplest of the La Alberca costumes. The wide, round, brightly coloured, pink, yellow and green "sayas" are the basis of this costume. They are adorned with shells, overlays, beads and sequins of many colours, to make them more colourful.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','sayas','The apron, embroidered and brightly coloured, covers the sackcloth. On the upper part, a shirt is worn that goes inside the saya and is covered with the manila shawl, giving the saya costume a greater attraction. The manila shawl, although not originally from the area, is a very important part of most of the costumes from the mountains, where we can find them with very different designs and in an infinite number of colours.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, nombreTraje, descrArte) VALUES ('trajes','en','sayas','Finally, after the manila shawl, the gold threads with crosses and galapagos are placed. These go on top of the shawl and are tied around the neck with coloured ribbons that give the final touch to this costume.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('trajemasc','en', 'The men suit is completely different from the women. The first thing the albercan men wear is a wide, white linen nightdress. The high collar of the nightdress is marked with a cross-stitch pattern, which the "labreras" call "ojito amarillo" (little yellow eye), and is closed at the front with a cufflink made of two large gold buttons.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('trajemasc','en', 'Over the long breeches, also made of linen, goes the blue or black velvet breeches. It is fastened at the waist, at the front, with a silver button, and a thin goatskin strap, which starts at the kidneys, is knotted at the navel. The breeches are narrowed at the bottom of the legs, and can be tightened below the knees with silver buttons or left open, leaving the silver buttons and pendants, called "follajes", loose, so that they can chime as they walk. There is another type of breeches, called "bombacho", which does not narrow at the knees, but is always open and is worn with high boots.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('trajemasc','en', 'To cover the legs, they wear socks, which are usually made of white thread, without feet. Ecru cloth leggings are worn over the shoes. The waistcoat, which is made of velvet (blue or black) with a double row of silver buttons, one to close the chest, although it is only buttoned halfway, and the other for decoration, is a must. The jacket, made of short terry cloth or velvet, is worn over the waistcoat, with silver buttons.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('trajemasc','en', 'Finally, the head is wrapped with a silk scarf, in Moorish style, and a hat can be added on top of it. And the waist, with a red sash ending in fringes that fall in front.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('orfebreria','en','The 18th century was the historical period of greatest splendour in La Alberca, and this is demonstrated by the rich jewellery that accompanies the traditional costumes that are still preserved and are exhibited on the days of festivals and celebrations. They are made of fine materials, gold and silver, and bear iconographic engravings, with plant, animal and geometric motifs, and even reliquaries with holy cards of virgins and saints, photos of family members, etc.');
INSERT INTO artesania (catArte, idioma, descrArte) VALUES ('orfebreria','en','The jewellery consists of gold threads with beads that can be round or oval and of different sizes. Earrings can be hoop earrings, pear-shaped earrings. Galapagos, diamond crosses, gold crystals, scallops and rings are also part of the gold and silver work of La Alberca.');
